action: Emodin can inhibit metastasis by interfering with the activity of matrix metalloproteinases, either directly or through through inhibition of focal adhesion kinase, mitogen-activated protein kinase, and RAC-alpha serine/threonine-protein kinase activation, and partial inhibition of transcription factor AP-1 and nuclear factor NF-kappa-B (NF-kb) transcriptional activities. emodin's antiinflammatory action is also due to its specific inhibition of the transcription factor NF-kb. (A3043, A3049, A3050)
